Nguyễn Hoàng Sang is an Intern Software Engineer with 0.33 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in developing fullstack applications leveraging microservices architecture, RESTful API design, and WebSocket communication, with a strong understanding of OOP, Design Patterns, JWT for authentication, and Email Verification. They are proficient in Agile and Scrum methodologies. Commercially, Sang gained hands-on experience as an ERP Programmer Intern at FPT IS, specializing in Oracle ERP systems, including Inventory Management (INV), Accounts Payable (AP), Accounts Receivable (AR), Purchase Order (PO), and Order Management (OM) modules, alongside utilizing Oracle reporting tools like BI Publisher, XML Publisher, and Form Builder for report development and form modification. Academically, Sang has developed a fullstack Event Management App incorporating ReactNative, TypeScript, NestJS, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Firebase, RabbitMQ, Docker, and GitHub Actions, and contributed to an e-commerce platform (NHA TRANG SEA FOOD) using React, ExpressJS, Node.js, AWS S3, and MoMo payment integration, as well as a WEB MOVIE application with ReactJS, NestJS, and MongoDB.
Technically, Sang is proficient in programming languages such as Javascript, Java, and Typescript. Their framework and library expertise includes NestJs, ReactJs, ExpressJs, ReactNative, NextJs, Redux Toolkit, Axios, MUI (Material UI), and Node.js. They possess hands-on experience with various databases including Mongodb, SQL server, MySQL, Postgresql, and Firebase. For DevOps and Cloud operations, Sang has worked with Docker, GitHub Actions, AWS S3, Vercel, and Google Cloud. Key tools and platforms in their arsenal include Git, Postman, Clerk, MoMo, and RabbitMQ. With an Agile-Scrum certification and an Intermediate (B1) English proficiency, Sang is pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Software Engineering, demonstrating a solid foundation in modern web development, enterprise resource planning, and payment integration domains.